Fragment of a saltglazed stoneware round-bottomed bottle (Hamilton bottle) bearing the stamped mark: Bathgate & Co. Calcutta. Bathgate & Co. was a chemist and druggist company in Calcutta which began its business in 1811 and likely lasted until early 1900s (ca. 1904). The bottle was used for soda water.
